# --- LLM provider (optional) -------------------------------------------------
# The agent is provider-agnostic. With NO key set it runs a built-in, grounded
# "mock" assistant so everything is demoable. Set ONE of the following to enable
# a real conversational agent — no code changes required.
# Provider priority: Nemotron → OpenAI → Anthropic → Ollama → mock.

# NVIDIA Nemotron NIM (OpenAI-compatible) — runs the agent + demand forecasts.
# Point this at a Nemotron model served locally on the GX10 / DGX Spark, OR at
# NVIDIA's hosted NGC endpoint (build.nvidia.com / NGC). The NGC catalog is
# OpenAI-compatible, so wiring a fine-tuned Nemotron is zero-code — just set:
#   NEMOTRON_BASE_URL=https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1   # NGC hosted
#   NEMOTRON_MODEL=<your fine-tuned model id from NGC>
#   NEMOTRON_API_KEY=nvapi-...                              # your NGC API key
# For a local NIM container instead:
#   NEMOTRON_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000/v1
#   NEMOTRON_MODEL=nvidia/llama-3.3-nemotron-super-49b-v1
#   (omit NEMOTRON_API_KEY for local)
# For Nemotron served via Ollama on the DGX (OpenAI-compatible /v1 endpoint).
# Run the app ON the DGX so Ollama stays local — open http://<DGX_IP>:3100/app
# from any LAN browser. Use the OpenAI-compatible /v1 path (NOT /api/chat) so the
# nemotron adapter strips <think> reasoning traces:
#   NEMOTRON_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
#   NEMOTRON_MODEL=Nemotron-3-nano:30b   # exact `ollama list` tag
#   (omit NEMOTRON_API_KEY for local Ollama)
# NEMOTRON_BASE_URL=
# NEMOTRON_MODEL=
# NEMOTRON_API_KEY=

# OpenAI
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# Anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-3-5-sonnet-latest

# Local Ollama
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1

# --- Events providers (optional) ---------------------------------------------
# Concerts, games, festivals & big events. ESPN pro-sports schedules work with
# NO key. Add either key below to enrich the feed with venue-precise concerts
# and demand-ranked events; without them those adapters stay disabled and the
# events panel falls back to ESPN + demo data.

# Ticketmaster Discovery API (free): https://developer.ticketmaster.com/
# TICKETMASTER_API_KEY=

# PredictHQ demand intelligence (rank + predicted attendance): https://www.predicthq.com/
# PREDICTHQ_TOKEN=

# --- Traffic (optional) ------------------------------------------------------
# Live road congestion traces (Waze-style red/amber/green). With NO key the map
# shows a time-of-day-weighted synthetic congestion model on real arteries. Add
# a TomTom key for live segment speeds. https://developer.tomtom.com/
# TOMTOM_API_KEY=

# --- Flights (optional) ------------------------------------------------------
# Aircraft inflow to YYZ works with NO key via OpenSky (live aircraft count).
# Add an aviationstack key for scheduled arrivals with airline/terminal detail.
# https://aviationstack.com/
# AVIATIONSTACK_KEY=

# --- Places (optional) -------------------------------------------------------
# Google Places API (New) — nearby business density, category mix, ratings and
# review volume around a location. Used as a static "commercial gravity" feature
# for demand forecasting + dataset enrichment. With NO key the enrichment falls
# back to the Toronto business-licences open dataset (real, no key) for density.
# Enable "Places API (New)" in Google Cloud. https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/places/web-service
# GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=

# --- GO Transit (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# GO Train route lines + trains render with NO key: geometry and the timetable
# come from the bundled GO GTFS extract (server/data/go-gtfs.json, built by
# scripts/build-go-gtfs.py). Trains are a schedule-accurate simulation — they
# run only during real service hours, at real frequency. Add a free Metrolinx
# Open Data key to swap in true GTFS-RT real-time vehicle positions.
# Register at https://www.metrolinx.com/en/aboutus/opendata/
# METROLINX_API_KEY=

# --- Server ------------------------------------------------------------------
# PORT=8787
